   "source": [
    "# AI-Driven Dynamic Pricing System for Delivery Services\n",
    "### A Deep Learning Approach to Revenue Optimization\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "*By Abdulrahman Jaber Ageeli, June 2026*\n",
    "\n",
    "**University:** Umm Al-Qura University  \n",
    "**Course:** Deep Learning Project\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Introduction\n",
    "\n",
    "One of the key challenges in delivery platforms is determining the optimal price for each order. The price must balance two competing objectives: maximizing revenue while maintaining a high probability of customer acceptance.\n",
    "\n",
    "Traditional pricing approaches rely on fixed rules or simple heuristics, which fail to capture the complex relationship between price, demand, and contextual factors.\n",
    "\n",
    "This project proposes an AI-driven solution that models customer behavior using deep learning and applies it to optimize pricing decisions dynamically.\n",
    "\n",
    "The core idea is to estimate the probability of acceptance and use it to maximize expected revenue:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{Expected Revenue} = \\text{Price} \\times P(\\text{accept})$$\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Methodology\n",
    "\n",
    "The system is implemented through a structured pipeline consisting of data preparation, simulation, modeling, and optimization.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.1 Feature Engineering\n",
    "\n",
    "Key features are derived from the dataset:\n",
    "- Delivery distance\n",
    "- Peak hour indicator\n",
    "- Weather condition (simulated)\n",
    "- Base price\n",
    "\n",
    "The base price is defined as:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$p_{base} = 8 + 0.8 \\times \\text{distance}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.2 Market Simulation\n",
    "\n",
    "Since real customer decisions are not available, a simulated market is created.\n",
    "\n",
    "Customer acceptance is modeled using a logistic function:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$P(\\text{accept}) = \\frac{1}{1 + e^{-z}}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "Where:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$z = -\\alpha (price - p_{base}) + \\epsilon$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The sensitivity parameter $\\alpha$ depends on context:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\alpha = 0.15 + 0.05d + 0.02d^2 + 0.08d \\cdot \\text{rain} - 0.07 \\cdot \\text{peak}$$\n",
    "\n",
    "This formulation allows the model to capture non-linear demand behavior.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.3 Model Training\n",
    "\n",
    "Two models are used:\n",
    "- Logistic Regression as a baseline\n",
    "- Deep Neural Network for non-linear modeling\n",
    "\n",
    "The neural network uses:\n",
    "- ReLU activation functions\n",
    "- Batch normalization\n",
    "- Dropout and L2 regularization\n",
    "- Early stopping to prevent overfitting\n",
    "\n",
    "### 2.4 Optimization Strategy\n",
    "\n",
    "The trained model is used to evaluate multiple price options and select the one that maximizes expected revenue:\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\\text{Optimal Price} = \\arg\\max_p (p \\times P(\\text{accept} | p))$$\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Sample Output\n",
    "\n",
    "The table below shows a sample of the optimized pricing decisions.\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "distance_km  p_base  Optimal_Price  Strategy\n",
    "3.44         10.75       8.23        Demand Stimulation\n",
    "5.62         12.49      10.07        Demand Stimulation\n",
    "5.18         12.15       9.79        Demand Stimulation\n",
    "2.95         10.36       7.93        Demand Stimulation\n",
    "7.38         13.91      12.34        Demand Stimulation\n",
    "8.97         15.18      13.78        Demand Stimulation\n",
    "8.73         14.98      13.30        Demand Stimulation\n",
    "6.52         13.21      11.46        Demand Stimulation\n",
    "2.94         10.35       7.92        Demand Stimulation\n",
    "5.38         12.31       9.67        Demand Stimulation\n",
    "```\n",
    "\n",
    "### Interpretation\n",
    "\n",
    "- In all cases, the optimal price is lower than the base price.\n",
    "- This indicates a price-sensitive market where reducing price increases acceptance probability significantly.\n",
    "- The strategy applied here is \"Demand Stimulation\", which focuses on increasing conversions.\n",
    "\n",
    "In other scenarios, the model may apply a \"Premium Strategy\" when demand is less sensitive to price.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Results and Insights\n",
    "\n",
    "The system demonstrates strong performance in both prediction and decision-making:\n",
    "\n",
    "- The deep neural network outperforms logistic regression in capturing non-linear relationships.\n",
    "- Calibration ensures that predicted probabilities are reliable.\n",
    "- The optimization process leads to significant revenue improvement compared to fixed pricing.\n",
    "\n",
    "The key insight is that pricing should adapt dynamically based on context rather than relying on static rules.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
